  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">1. Google Sheets & Microsoft Excel Templates</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    While not strictly "software" in the standalone sense, spreadsheet templates remain the most popular <strong>free construction cost estimating software</strong> for small businesses. They are highly customizable and familiar to most users.
  </p>
  
  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">2. STACK (Free Tier)</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    STACK offers a robust cloud-based takeoff and estimating platform. While their full suite is paid, they often provide a limited free version or trial that is perfect for smaller residential projects.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">3. Estimating Edge (Trial Mode)</h3>
  <p class="mb-4">
    For more complex trades like roofing or flooring, Estimating Edge provides specialized tools. Their trial periods are an excellent way to see how dedicated estimating software can improve your speed and accuracy.
